---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SchemaMarkup from '../../components/SchemaMarkup.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import TidyCalEmbed from '../../components/TidyCalEmbed.astro';
import { PHONE, YOUTUBE_URL, GBP_URL } from '../../consts';

const faqs = [
	{
		question: "How much is my Austin home worth?",
		answer: "Your home's value depends on location, condition, size, recent upgrades, and comparable sales in your immediate area. I provide a free, data-driven market analysis using current MLS data — not an algorithm estimate like Zillow. Contact me for a personalized home valuation and I'll walk you through the comparables.",
	},
	{
		question: "How long does it take to sell a home in Austin?",
		answer: "The average days on market in Austin varies by neighborhood and price point, but well-priced homes in good condition typically sell within 30-60 days. Proper pricing from day one is the single biggest factor in selling quickly. Overpriced homes sit on the market, go stale, and eventually sell for less than they would have with accurate initial pricing.",
	},
	{
		question: "What does it cost to sell a home in Austin?",
		answer: "Typical seller costs include agent commissions (negotiable after the 2024 NAR settlement), title insurance owner's policy (paid by the seller in Texas), HOA transfer fees, any agreed-upon buyer credits or repairs, and prorated property taxes. I'll give you a full net sheet estimate before you list so there are no surprises at closing.",
	},
	{
		question: "Should I sell my Austin home now or wait?",
		answer: "It depends on your personal situation — your timeline, why you're selling, and what you plan to do next. The Austin market in 2026 is more balanced than the 2021-2022 peak, but well-priced homes still sell. If you're moving for a job, family, or lifestyle reasons, the 'right time' is when it works for your life. I'll give you honest advice without pressure.",
	},
	{
		question: "Do I need to stage my Austin home before listing?",
		answer: "Not every home needs professional staging. Vacant or cluttered homes benefit the most. Occupied homes usually just need decluttering, depersonalization, and minor touch-ups. I'll walk through your home and tell you honestly what moves the needle and what's a waste of money for your specific property.",
	},
	{
		question: "What improvements should I make before selling in Austin?",
		answer: "The best ROI improvements are usually the small ones: fresh paint in neutral colors, deep cleaning, landscaping cleanup, minor plumbing and electrical fixes, and replacing worn fixtures. Major renovations (full kitchen, adding square footage) rarely return their cost. I can do a pre-listing walkthrough and give you a specific list.",
	},
	{
		question: "Should I get a pre-listing inspection?",
		answer: "For older homes, yes — it's often worth it. A pre-listing inspection lets you address issues on your own timeline and disclose them upfront, which reduces the risk of a buyer backing out after their inspection or demanding large credits. For newer or well-maintained homes, it's usually not necessary.",
	},
	{
		question: "How do you market Austin homes differently?",
		answer: "Every listing includes professional photography, an MLS listing written for both buyers and search engines, a YouTube video tour on my English-language channel, and targeted social media promotion. YouTube in particular reaches out-of-state relocation buyers who are researching Austin before they arrive — a huge and growing segment.",
	},
	{
		question: "Can I sell my Austin home without a real estate agent?",
		answer: "You can (it's called FSBO — For Sale By Owner), but data consistently shows agent-listed homes sell for more, even after commissions. The reasons are pricing expertise, MLS exposure, buyer-agent network, professional marketing, and negotiation. If you want to explore FSBO, I'm happy to explain the tradeoffs honestly.",
	},
	{
		question: "What's the difference between list price and sale price in Austin?",
		answer: "As of 2026, most Austin homes sell at or slightly below list price, a big shift from 2021 when multiple-offer situations pushed homes 10-20% over list. The sale-to-list ratio varies by price point and neighborhood — I'll share current data for your specific area when we talk.",
	},
	{
		question: "How does the NAR settlement affect selling my Austin home?",
		answer: "The 2024 NAR settlement changed how buyer-agent compensation is handled. As a seller, you're no longer required to offer buyer-agent compensation through the MLS, but most sellers still choose to because it broadens the buyer pool. I'll walk you through the tradeoffs and recommend what's best for your specific situation.",
	},
	{
		question: "What are closing costs for sellers in Austin?",
		answer: "Seller closing costs in Austin typically include the owner's title insurance policy (around 0.5-0.9% of sale price in Texas), any agreed-upon commissions, HOA transfer fees, survey (if required), prorated property taxes, and attorney or escrow fees. On a $500,000 sale, budget roughly 1-2% of the sale price in closing costs on top of any commissions.",
	},
	{
		question: "How do property taxes work when I sell my Austin home?",
		answer: "Texas property taxes are prorated at closing. You'll pay your share of the current year's taxes up to the closing date, and the buyer takes over from there. If you've been claiming a homestead exemption, it stays with the property for the remainder of the tax year but typically can't transfer to your next home until you claim a new homestead there.",
	},
	{
		question: "Can I sell my Austin home while buying another?",
		answer: "Yes — it's common. Options include: sell first and rent temporarily, buy first with a bridge loan or HELOC, or negotiate a leaseback so you can stay in your current home after closing. I handle both sides and coordinate timing so there's no gap. We'll map out the best approach for your situation.",
	},
	{
		question: "What happens at a typical Austin closing?",
		answer: "In Texas, closings happen at a title company, not an attorney's office. You'll review and sign documents (deed, settlement statement, payoff, etc.), turn over keys and remotes, and the funds will be wired to the title company then disbursed. Most closings take 30-60 minutes. I'll be there with you.",
	},
	{
		question: "How do I start the selling process in Austin?",
		answer: "Start with a free home valuation conversation. I'll run the comparables for your neighborhood, walk through your home, and give you an honest price range and timeline. No obligation, no pressure. From there, if we move forward, we'll agree on pricing, marketing, and a listing date.",
	},
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Sell My House in Austin, TX — Get a Free Home Valuation | 512 Austin Home" description="Sell your home in Austin, TX. Free home valuation, professional video marketing, data-driven pricing. Call (512) 766-3188 for a no-obligation consultation with listing agent William Zhang.">
	<SchemaMarkup type="agent" />
	<SchemaMarkup type="faq" data={{ questions: faqs }} />
	<SchemaMarkup type="breadcrumb" data={{ items: [
		{ name: 'Home', url: '/' },
		{ name: 'Sell My House in Austin', url: '/sell/' },
	] }} />

	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 py-16">

		<!-- ABOVE THE FOLD: H1 + CTA -->
		<header class="mb-6">
			<h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-primary tracking-tight mb-4">Sell My House in Austin, TX</h1>
			<p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-text-muted max-w-2xl mb-8">Get a free home valuation and a transparent plan to sell your Austin home for top dollar. No pressure, no obligation.</p>

			<div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mb-4">
				<a href="#schedule" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-white bg-accent rounded-lg hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all no-underline">
					Get Your Free Home Valuation
				</a>
				<a href={`tel:${PHONE.replace(/[^0-9+]/g, '')}`} class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-accent border-2 border-accent rounded-lg hover:bg-accent-light transition-all no-underline">
					Call {PHONE}
				</a>
			</div>
			<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">15-minute call. I'll pull comps for your address before we talk.</p>
		</header>

		<!-- SOCIAL PROOF -->
		<div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6 mb-16">
			<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
				<div class="flex text-amber-400 text-lg" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars">
					<span>&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</span>
				</div>
				<span class="text-sm text-text-muted">5.0 rating &middot; <a href={GBP_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent no-underline hover:underline">Google Reviews</a></span>
			</div>
			<blockquote class="text-sm text-text-muted italic leading-relaxed">
				"William communicated with the seller's agent, analyzed the seller's needs, and crafted an offer that appealed to them most. My offer wasn't the highest, but we won because of his strategy. Best agent."
			</blockquote>
			<p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2">— Verified Google Reviewer, Austin TX</p>
		</div>

		<!-- WHAT YOU GET — scannable cards, not prose -->
		<section class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">What You Get When You List with Me</h2>
			<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
				<div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
					<h3 class="font-display text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">Data-Driven Pricing</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Pricing based on current MLS comps, not gut feel. Homes priced right from day one sell faster and for more money. I'll show you exactly how I arrived at the number.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
					<h3 class="font-display text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">YouTube Video Marketing</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Every listing gets a professional video tour on <a href={YOUTUBE_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent no-underline hover:underline">YouTube</a>. This reaches out-of-state relocation buyers who are researching Austin online — a huge and growing segment that traditional marketing misses.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
					<h3 class="font-display text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">Professional Photography</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">High-quality photos are the first impression buyers get. Every listing includes professional photography that showcases your home's best features and brings in more showings.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
					<h3 class="font-display text-base font-bold text-primary mb-2">Full Net Sheet Before You List</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">You'll know exactly what you'll walk away with. I provide a detailed net sheet covering commissions, title costs, taxes, and fees so there are zero surprises at closing.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- PROCESS — concise -->
		<section class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">How It Works</h2>
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
					<div>
						<h3 class="font-display font-bold text-primary mb-1">Free Home Valuation Call</h3>
						<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">I pull comps for your address, analyze your neighborhood's current market, and give you an honest price range. 15 minutes, no obligation.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
					<div>
						<h3 class="font-display font-bold text-primary mb-1">Prep and List</h3>
						<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">I walk your home and tell you what's worth fixing and what's a waste of money. Then we shoot photos, record the video tour, and go live on MLS.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
					<div>
						<h3 class="font-display font-bold text-primary mb-1">Showings and Offers</h3>
						<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">I manage showings and relay feedback the same day. When offers come in, I break down price, terms, contingencies, and financing strength so you can compare clearly.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
					<div>
						<h3 class="font-display font-bold text-primary mb-1">Negotiate and Close</h3>
						<p class="text-sm text-text-muted">From inspection negotiations to closing coordination, I handle everything. You show up at the title company, sign, and walk away with a check.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- MID-PAGE CTA -->
		<div class="bg-accent-light rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-8 mb-16 border-l-4 border-accent">
			<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Thinking About Selling?</h2>
			<p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-4">Most sellers I work with start with a 15-minute call to get a realistic price range. No listing agreement, no commitment — just the numbers.</p>
			<div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
				<a href="#schedule" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white bg-accent rounded-lg hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all no-underline">
					Schedule Your Free Valuation
				</a>
				<a href={`tel:${PHONE.replace(/[^0-9+]/g, '')}`} class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-accent border-2 border-accent rounded-lg hover:bg-white transition-all no-underline">
					Call {PHONE}
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-8">Austin Home Selling FAQ</h2>
			<div class="space-y-4">
				{faqs.map((f, i) => (
					<details class="bg-surface rounded-xl border border-border p-6 group" open={i === 0}>
						<summary class="font-display font-semibold text-primary cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
							{f.question}
							<span class="text-text-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0">&#9662;</span>
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">{f.answer}</p>
					</details>
				))}
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- TIDYCAL SCHEDULING -->
		<div id="schedule" class="mb-10 scroll-mt-20">
			<TidyCalEmbed
				heading="Schedule Your Free Home Valuation"
				subheading="Pick a time that works. I'll pull comps for your address before we talk — you'll get a realistic price range and a clear plan, no pressure."
			/>
		</div>

		<!-- CONTACT FORM FALLBACK -->
		<ContactForm heading="Prefer to message first?" subheading="Tell me your address and timeline. I'll send you a market snapshot and we'll go from there." />
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
